block subSubContent
	h3
		b Intro
	p Consider a multivariate function.
	p \(f(x)\).
	p We can define:
	p \(\Delta f(x, \Delta x):=f(x+\Delta x)-f(x)\)
	p \(\Delta f(x, \Delta x)=\sum_{i=1}^nf(x+\Delta x_i+\sum_{j=0}^{i-1}\Delta x_j)-f(x+\sum_{j=0}^{i-1}\Delta x_j)\)
	p \(\Delta f(x, \Delta x)=\sum_{i=1}^n\Delta x_i \frac{f(x+\Delta x_i+\sum_{j=0}^{i-1}\Delta x_j)-f(x+\sum_{j=0}^{i-1}\Delta x_j)}{\Delta x_i}\)
	p \(\frac{\Delta f}{\Delta x_k}=\sum_{i=1}^n\frac{\Delta x_i}{\Delta x_k} \frac{f(x+\Delta x_i+\sum_{j=0}^{i-1}\Delta x_j)-f(x+\sum_{j=0}^{i-1}\Delta x_j)}{\Delta x_i}\)
	p \(\lim_{\Delta x_k \rightarrow 0}\frac{\Delta f}{\Delta x_k}=\sum_{i=1}^n\lim_{\Delta x_k \rightarrow 0}\frac{\Delta x_i}{\Delta x_k} \frac{f(x+\Delta x_i+\sum_{j=0}^{i-1}\Delta x_j)-f(x+\sum_{j=0}^{i-1}\Delta x_j)}{\Delta x_i}\)
	p \(\frac{df}{dx_k}=\sum_{i=1}^n\frac{dx_i}{dx_k} \frac{\delta f}{\delta x_i}\)
	h3
		b Total differentiation of a univariate function
	p For a univariate function total differentiation is the same as partial differentiation.
	p \(\frac{df}{dx}=\frac{dx}{dx} \frac{\delta f}{\delta x}\)
	p \(\frac{df}{dx}=\frac{\delta f}{\delta x}\)
